# Disclaimer Gate Implementation Plan

A prominent disclaimer is required before users can access the content of GasCrisis.net. This will act as a "gatekeeper" to ensure users acknowledge that the site is for reference only and not a substitute for clinical judgment.

## Proposed Changes

### [index.html](file:///C:/Users/jbvan/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/gascrisis_net/index.html)
- [NEW] Add a new full-screen modal `div` with the ID `disclaimer-modal`.
- The modal will contain the disclaimer text and a prominent "I Agree / Enter Site" button.

### [styles.css](file:///C:/Users/jbvan/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/gascrisis_net/styles.css)
- [NEW] Add styles for `#disclaimer-modal` to make it a fixed overlay (`z-index: 2000`) with a blurred background (`backdrop-filter`) that completely obscures the main content until dismissed.
- Add styles for the disclaimer content box and the prominent "Agree" button.

### [script.js](file:///C:/Users/jbvan/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/gascrisis_net/script.js)
- [MODIFY] Add logic to check `localStorage` to see if the user has already accepted the disclaimer (so they don't see it on every single page load, but rather once per device/session, depending on preference).
- If not accepted, display the `#disclaimer-modal`.
- Add an event listener to the "Agree" button to hide the main modal and save the acceptance state in `localStorage`.

## User Review Required
None required right now, the implementation follows standard web practices for disclaimers. The user can adjust the exact wording of the disclaimer text after the structure is implemented.

## Verification Plan
1. **Manual Verification**: Open the website in the browser. 
2. Verify the disclaimer pops up immediately and prevents interaction with the background.
3. Click "Agree". Verify the modal disappears.
4. Refresh the page. Verify the modal does *not* reappear (due to `localStorage`).
